gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nuggets 142, Hawks 110
gameRecap.excerpt: Denver defeats Atlanta, 142-110. For Denver, Nikola Jokic led the way with 19 points, 14 rebounds, 11 assists, and two steals while aided by Kentavious Caldwell-Pope (24 points, two steals, six 3PM) in the victory. Clint Capela finished with 19 points and 12 rebounds with Jalen Johnson recording 17 points, six rebounds, and four assists for Atlanta in the losing effort. Denver improves to 54-24, while Atlanta moves to 36-42 with the loss.
